Egyptian billionaire Naguib Sawiris wants Greece and Italy to sell him an island in the Mediterranean to help hundreds of thousands of people fleeing from Syria and other conflicts. Sawiris announced the initiative on Twitter saying, \"Greece or Italy sell me an island, I\'ll call its independence and host the migrants and provide jobs for them building their new country.\" We look at the plan on the Lip News with Margaret Howell and Jose Marcelino Ortiz.

