Egyptian billionaire Naguib Sawiris wants to buy an island off the coast of Italy or Greece to house among the hundreds of thousands of refugees crossing the Mediterranean at the risk of their own lives. \"Greece or Italy, sell me an island, I declare it independent, get there the refugees and allow them to participate in building their new country,\" as tweeted wealthy businessman. \"And that\'s really feasible,\" he said today at the French news agency AFP. \"There are dozens of islands that leave hundreds of thousands of refugees can receive.\" Since early this year, more than 350,000 people fleeing poverty or conflict in their country of origin and have crossed the Mediterranean in the hope of a better life in Europe. More than 2,600 of them do not survive the adventure. Sawiris confirmed by an Egyptian private television that he will contact the Italian and Greek governments to concretize his idea. In Greece, which holds a forced sale of state assets, this should pose few problems.

He estimates its cost at between \"10 and 100 million dollars\", but thinks that the \"main issue is the investment in infrastructure\" will be. \"There will be temporary stays to accommodate people and then you give them work in the construction of homes, schools, universities and hospitals.\" \"But if the situation improves in their own country, the person who wants to return, according to the businessman, whose family in Egypt, the popular artificial resort of El Gouna has developed on the shores of the Red Sea.

